-{"id":"bd-3vx8","title":"Optimize runtime install phases (apt/bun/cargo/etc) based on profiling","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-21T19:00:39.996743538Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-21T19:20:57.030161692Z","closed_at":"2026-01-21T19:20:57.030111017Z","close_reason":"Implemented batched cargo install optimization in install_languages_legacy_tools. Previously, 5 cargo tools (du-dust, lsd, bat, fd-find, ripgrep) were installed sequentially, each requiring separate index download and dependency resolution. Now they are collected and batch-installed in a single cargo install command, which: (1) downloads the crate index once instead of 5x, (2) resolves dependencies once, (3) allows cargo to parallelize compilation. Includes fallback to individual installs if batch fails.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-3vx8","depends_on_id":"bd-2z32","type":"discovered-from","created_at":"2026-01-21T19:00:40.029703844Z","created_by":"ubuntu"}]}
